# SeatSense Project Rules

## Technology Stack
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Prisma ORM
- Tailwind CSS
- React Server Components (default)

## Code Style
- Use 'use client' only when necessary (forms, interactive components)
- Prefer Server Actions over API routes
- Use Server Components for data fetching
- Always use TypeScript types (no `any`)

## Database
- Prisma for all database operations
- Include relations in queries to avoid N+1
- Use transactions for multi-step operations

## Components
- Server Components: Default for static content
- Client Components: Forms, interactive elements only
- Use Tailwind utility classes, avoid custom CSS
- Components should be small and focused

## Best Practices
- No hardcoded values - use constants
- Comment complex business logic
- Handle errors gracefully with try/catch
- Use revalidatePath after mutations
